  "title": "Senior Mechanical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Senior MECHANICAL\nENGINEER</strong></u></p><p>·        \nResponsible for design and development of electronic,\nIoT\nproducts to achieve technical, schedule and cost goals.</p><p>·        \nResponsible for electro-mechanical (LCD,\ntransducer), plastic, metal and rubber parts design and assembly qualification.</p><p>·        \nPerform engineering tests and evaluations to\nensure compliance to product specifications and initiate design changes as\nnecessary.</p><p>·        \nWork with suppliers to achieve product specification\nand cost goals. </p><p><u>The requirements</u></p><p>*     \nBachelors or Master’s Degree in Mechanical\nEngineering or related field.</p><p>*     \nMinimum 3 years of mechanical design\nexperience, preferably in consumer electronics, IoT devices, or compact\nelectromechanically parts.</p><p>*     \nProven experience in full product development\nlifecycle: concept, prototyping, DFM/DFA, tooling, and production</p><p>*     \nProficiency in Creo Elements/Pro or Solidworks\nCAD software.</p><p>*     \nThermal and structure analysis.</p><p>*     \nTolerance analysis and Geometric Dimensioning\nand Tolerancing (GD&T)</p><p>*     \nExperience with DFM/DFA</p><p>*     \nKnowledge of IP-rated enclosures for waterproof/dustproof\ndevices</p><p>*     \nIntegration with electronics: understanding\nPCB layout impacts, thermal management, and connector selection.</p><p>*     \nKnowledge of prototyping techniques: 3D\nprinting, CNC, injection molding etc.</p><p>*     \nExperience working with environmental and reliability\ntesting such as drop test, thermal cycling , and vibration</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
